commit_message:
Virtual guest device role tagging

This will provide a mechanism for the user to tag a device they
have assigned to their guest with a specific role. The tag will
be matched to the hardware address of the device and this mapping
exposed to the guest OS via metadata service/cloud-init

Spec for bp/virt-device-tagged-attach-detach

APIImpact

Previously-approved: Newton
Change-Id: Idcac1506b61c29f02e335200fb18d394243098e2

the tenant is already bound to a pod, and the pod is exactly the pod

commit_message:
The framework of dynamic pod binding

1. What is the problem?
In the Tricircle, each tenant is bound to multiple pods,
where it creates various types of resources. However such a binding
relationship should be dynamic instead of static. For instance when
some resources in a pod are exhausted, tenant needs to be bound to a
new pod in same AZ.

2. What is the solution to the problem?
To deal with the above problem, the Tricircle dynamically bind tenants
to pod which has available resources. We call this feature dynamic pod
binding, which is explained in https://review.openstack.org/#/c/306224/
in detail. In this patch, we only try to binds a tenant to a pod
dynamically, when she tries to create a VM.

3. What the features need to be implemented to the Tricircle to realize
the solution?
When a tenant creates a VM, the Tricircle first selects all available
pods for her. Then by filtering and weighing the pods, the Tricircle
selects the most suitable pod for the tenant. Next, the Tricircle query
database for current binding relationship of the tenant. If the tenant
is not bound to any pod, we create a new binding relationship, which
binds the tenant to the selected pod. If the tenant is already bound to
a pod, and the pod is not the pod selected by the Tricircle, we update
current binding relationship, which binds the tenant to a new pod. If
the tenant is already bound to a pod, and the pod is exactly the pod
selected by the Tricircle, the Tricircle does noting.

Change-Id: I3972e6799f78da6ec35be556487f79b1234731b8

commit_message:
Allow p-o-i to install itself from current source when used without Zuul

puppet-openstack-integration currently takes care of installing itself.
This is done through the Puppetfile which references the p-o-i repository.

This works with zuul-cloner because Zuul with ensure the current reference
is cloned.
However, when running outside of the gate, this means that p-o-i will
completely disregard any local code and instead install from the git source
specified in the Puppetfile.

Change-Id: I665347dbede2c53bd5537d4a29d07bfe679c50e5
(cherry picked from commit c2551e61455ecbb66c2fe8aa5fae60817a0884b0)

subject: Add upgrade playbook to force nova flavor migrate
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-09-22 16:37:11.000000000', 'files': ['doc/source/upgrade-guide/manual-upgrade.rst', 'scripts/upgrade-utilities/playbooks/nova-flavor-migration.yml', 'scripts/run-upgrade.sh', 'releasenotes/notes/kilo-upgrade-nova-flavor-migrate-05402ab6faf1df1c.yaml'], 'message': "Add upgrade playbook to force nova flavor migrate

The nova-extra-migrations.yml upgrade playbook in kilo ran the
`nova-manage db migrate_flavor_data` command. This command always
returns a successful return code, regardless of whether or not any
migrations were performed.

Add an upgrade playbook that runs the command with the '--force' option to help
ensure that these required migrations are performed prior to installing
Liberty, where the command is no longer available.

Change-Id: If4e4241399346375811f128e8fa55d8d08343a10
Closes-bug: 1594584
"}]
commit_message:
Add upgrade playbook to force nova flavor migrate

The nova-extra-migrations.yml upgrade playbook in kilo ran the
`nova-manage db migrate_flavor_data` command. This command always
returns a successful return code, regardless of whether or not any
migrations were performed.

Add an upgrade playbook that runs the command with the '--force' option to help
ensure that these required migrations are performed prior to installing
Liberty, where the command is no longer available.

Change-Id: If4e4241399346375811f128e8fa55d8d08343a10
Closes-bug: 1594584

commit_message:
Not check subnet with dhcp disabled when get_isolated_subnets

[1] will only return subnets with dhcp enabled for dhcp agent. If there
is subnet with dhcp disabled in network, and the subnet is attached to
router, exception can be observed as bug described.

The fix here will just check the subnets that are in network in
dhcp-agent, when call get_isolated_subnets.

[1] http://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack/neutron/tree/neutron/api/rpc/handlers/dhcp_rpc.py#n141

Change-Id: I5e816c48d25efda9ea349210316c8f1ea5bdbcac
Closes-bug: #1582583

commit_message:
[WIP] Use ansible-playbook for zuul-worker element

This is a POC to see if we can use ansible-playbook as our
configuration management tool for our zuul-workers.

We'll be using the ansible-role-zuul role to setup zuul. Both creating
the zuul user and creating our virtualenv.

Change-Id: I9d951081555dfbdcd443f3cb53bcbbe416398b7e
Signed-off-by: Paul Belanger <pabelanger@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Add python-etcd 0.4.3

Zun needs this library to talk to etcd server.

* Is the library actively maintained?
  Yes, please see its github page [1] for detail.
  [1]https://github.com/jplana/python-etcd

* Is the library good code?
  I believe so.

* Is the library python 3 compatible?
  Yes, the code is tested against python3, see [2].
  [2]https://github.com/jplana/python-etcd/blob/0.4.3/.travis.yml#L4

* Is the library license compatible?
  Yes, the MIT License (MIT).

* Is the library already packaged in the distros we target (Ubuntu latest / Fedora latest)?
  No.

* Is the function of this library already covered by other libraries in global-requirements.txt?
  No.

* Is the library required for OpenStack project or related dev or infrastructure setup? (Answer to this should be Yes, of course) Which?
  Yes, Zun[3] needs it to talk to etcd server.
  [3]https://github.com/openstack/zun

Change-Id: I90fe078166cbad831da209ae3ff009e01d4e058c

commit_message:
[WIP] Implement event-notification-trigger spec
This is part 4 of 5 patch sets which implement the Mistral
event-notification-trigger spec. This is a work in progress.

This code was demonstrated in an IBM presentation given at the Austin
OpenStack Summit in 2016 entitled 'Using OpenStack to Clean up After
Itself: Automatically Run Mistral Workflows in Response to OpenStack
Notifications'.

The event notification service is added to Mistral. It gives Mistral
the capability to listen for specific notification events on the
AMQP bus, and start workflows when those notification events are
received. To facilitate this, support was added for an event trigger.
Event triggers are created by the user, and stored in the Mistral
database. They define the events to listen for, and the workflows to
execute when the events are received. A REST API and CLI are also
provided to create, modify, and delete event triggers.

This patch adds the python Mistral client changes to support the new
event trigger REST API and CLI.

Change-Id: Ic1309d080f65c4e7ff9935fcbbf4887c96c9b92a
Implements: blueprint event-notification-trigger

commit_message:
[WIP] Implement event-notification-trigger spec
This is part 5 of 5 patch sets which implement the Mistral
event-notification-trigger spec. This is a work in progress.

This code was demonstrated in an IBM presentation given at the Austin
OpenStack Summit in 2016 entitled 'Using OpenStack to Clean up After
Itself: Automatically Run Mistral Workflows in Response to OpenStack
Notifications'.

The event notification service is added to Mistral. It gives Mistral
the capability to listen for specific notification events on the
AMQP bus, and start workflows when those notification events are
received. To facilitate this, support was added for an event trigger.
Event triggers are created by the user, and stored in the Mistral
database. They define the events to listen for, and the workflows to
execute when the events are received. A REST API and CLI are also
provided to create, modify, and delete event triggers.

This patch adds the Mistral action changes including support for the
Glance Metadata Definitions APIs.

Change-Id: I24d897b4b48e615ed589ccd4a9e0c06d64bf782b
Implements: blueprint event-notification-trigger

commit_message:
Fix Launch Instance without Cinder

A previous patch altered the defaults in the angular Launch Instance,
but didn't account for those running without Cinder. This patch fixes
those assumptions.

Co-Authored-By: Rob Cresswell <robert.cresswell@outlook.com>
Change-Id: I8dc54fa40fa7eb8ae95a13741405f2a80337b33d
Closes-Bug: 1585761

commit_message:
Retain apt sources options during host bootstrap

When running the bootstrap-host playbook for an AIO install, the
apt/sources.list file is rewritten. Update the tasks determining
existing repos to make sure that any options, such as specific
architectures, are included in the rewritten file.

This is a combined manual backport of the following changes with the
addition of making sure repos are written as strings to user_variables.
I7fab8f3c072e25fa8138c3e37d764b36d17526d6
I7ecd9dc130d194342e236bef42b08926f98940fd

Change-Id: Ic1f842d66cb9d60f069eb323dd5c6e9d2779c9ba

commit_message:
Add iscsi port to sf_svip arg if not provided

With things like VLAN support it may be necessary for
an admin to specify the sf_svip (IP) address.  The problem
is that when this is specified if the admin forgets to include
the port suffix to the SVIP address it may not work on certain
distros (inparticular RHEL variants).

This patch just adds a simple check when the endpoint is created
to make sure the port suffix is included, if it's not it
automatically adds the default 3260.

NOTE: This is not a backport, the Cheesecake code has an

revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-09-24 18:18:43.000000000', 'files': ['keystoneclient/tests/unit/test_base.py', 'keystoneclient/base.py'], 'message': "Fix non-ascii attributes

It's possible to set and get custom attributes through the API, and
it's also possible to use any Unicode strings, not only ASCII range.
It works perfectly fine when accessing the API directly using
e.g. curl.

However, keystoneclient stumbles on the non-ascii keys because
it tries to set this as an attribute for the resource class and fails
because Python 2.7 does not support non-ascii identifiers:

https://docs.python.org/2.7/reference/lexical_analysis.html#identifiers

So change the logic to skip setting non-ascii attributes; they are still
available in the dict representation.

Closes-Bug: #1626403
Change-Id: I267188cdb1d303e3d0fb6bd3229b606f4fe9b2d8
"}]
commit_message:
Fix non-ascii attributes

It's possible to set and get custom attributes through the API, and
it's also possible to use any Unicode strings, not only ASCII range.
It works perfectly fine when accessing the API directly using
e.g. curl.

However, keystoneclient stumbles on the non-ascii keys because
it tries to set this as an attribute for the resource class and fails
because Python 2.7 does not support non-ascii identifiers:

https://docs.python.org/2.7/reference/lexical_analysis.html#identifiers

So change the logic to skip setting non-ascii attributes; they are still
available in the dict representation.

Closes-Bug: #1626403
Change-Id: I267188cdb1d303e3d0fb6bd3229b606f4fe9b2d8

commit_message:
Handle add/remove subports events loss due to agent failures

Upon restart the agent reconciles the logical with the physical
state by removing/adding physical subports that are used to
be/are current present in the logical view.

This patch adds a functional test to demonstrate that there's
no need to handle the resync in the trunk driver, since the ovs
agent already takes care of it.

Change-Id: I164153c79313f2ae7a1fca0414736d5987656185
Partially-implements: blueprint vlan-aware-vms
Partial-bug: #1623708

commit_message:
Register master node but make it non schedulable

master node is not registered in k8s_coreos, it should
register but should be marked as non schedulable.
This is done by adding following parameters to kubelet
args:-
    --register-node=true
    --register-schedulable=false

Change-Id: Ifc2d52dadc128f4e09cfe5b1bea924dae725cd7c
Closes-Bug: #1625581

commit_message:
Move restore auth parameters to restore_auth attr

Restore REST body includes the parameters attribute which specifies
each resource or resource type paramters according to protection
plugin's restore schema.
Restore target auth parameters (such as username and password) to be
sent in 'restore_auth' dictionary in the restore body and not saved
in the restore object.

Change-Id: I7e73d2a0f1d347e83c9bb412649533700bd35ea4

commit_message:
Bridge network, subnet clean during router deletion

1. What is the problem
To connect bottom routers in different pods, we need to create
bridge networks and subnets. These networks and subnets are not
deleted after bottom routers are deleted.

2. What is the solution to the problem
Clean these bridge networks and subnets during top router deletion.

3. What the features need to be implemented to the Tricircle
   to realize the solution
Bridge networks and subnets now can be cleaned up.

Change-Id: I1f2feb7cba3dda14350b3e25a3c33563379eb580

revisions:

- Is the library actively maintained?

Latest version is 10.3.5.0.1 released on 2016-08-08. Maintainers
are responsive in #dogtag-pki on freenode.
Also RedHat is using it for the "Red Hat Certificate System" product.

- Is the library good code?

I haven't looked into the code in detail but is has a testsuite (using tox
and pytest). In general, the code looks good to me.

- Is the library python 3 compatible?

Yes

- Is the library license compatible?

License is LGPLv3+ which is compatible.
Note: The library was relicensed *because* of the OpenStack license
requirements.

- Is the library already packaged in the distros we target (Ubuntu
latest / Fedora latest)?

Ubuntu:
Not yet. But given that it's a common python package it shouldn't be hard to
package it for Ubuntu.

Fedora:
Not yet. But given that it's a common python package it shouldn't be hard to
package it for Fedora.

Note: Both (Ubuntu and Fedora) have the server part of dogtag already packaged.

- Is the function of this library already covered by other libraries
in ``global-requirements.txt``?

No.

- Is the library required for OpenStack project or related dev or
infrastructure setup? (Answer to this should be Yes, of course)
Which?

Yes. It's used for the dogtag Barbican plugin.
See http://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack/barbican/tree/barbican/plugin/dogtag.py

Change-Id: Ibedae54e631e9c3d3726453adcd204ce96b19d77
'}]
commit_message:
Add dogtag-pki used by Barbican

- Is the library actively maintained?

Latest version is 10.3.5.0.1 released on 2016-08-08. Maintainers
are responsive in #dogtag-pki on freenode.
Also RedHat is using it for the "Red Hat Certificate System" product.

- Is the library good code?

I haven't looked into the code in detail but is has a testsuite (using tox
and pytest). In general, the code looks good to me.

- Is the library python 3 compatible?

Yes

- Is the library license compatible?

License is LGPLv3+ which is compatible.
Note: The library was relicensed *because* of the OpenStack license
requirements.

- Is the library already packaged in the distros we target (Ubuntu
latest / Fedora latest)?

Ubuntu:
Not yet. But given that it's a common python package it shouldn't be hard to
package it for Ubuntu.

Fedora:
Not yet. But given that it's a common python package it shouldn't be hard to
package it for Fedora.

Note: Both (Ubuntu and Fedora) have the server part of dogtag already packaged.

- Is the function of this library already covered by other libraries
in ``global-requirements.txt``?

No.

- Is the library required for OpenStack project or related dev or
infrastructure setup? (Answer to this should be Yes, of course)
Which?

Yes. It's used for the dogtag Barbican plugin.
See http://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack/barbican/tree/barbican/plugin/dogtag.py

Change-Id: Ibedae54e631e9c3d3726453adcd204ce96b19d77

commit_message:
Nova_APIGW Server Action Support(part2)

1. What is the problem
   The current Nova_APIGW does not support following server actions:
   reboot: Reboots a server.
   resize: Resizes a server.
   confirmResize: Confirms a pending resize action for a server.
   revertResize: Cancels and reverts a pending resize action for
                 a server.
   os-resetState: Resets the state of a server.

2. What is the solution to the problem
   Implement the above server action

3. What the features need to be implemented to the Tricircle
   to realize the solution
   Add the above server action

Change-Id: Ia3d0de1a42320cb1ee55b25210b227cb34a829a9

commit_message:
Change exception raised in graphics and serial check

Two of live migration prechecks, graphics and serial, raise
MigrationError exception when check fails. This results in
internal API error in API and instance is left in ERROR/MIGRATING
state.

This patch changes MigrationError to something more appropriate:
MigrationPreCheckError. This exception is handled by conductor
manager, so that VM state is reverted to the old one and correct
error is returned through API. Also rescheduling will be performed
to find another host which might have suitable configuration.

Change-Id: I2b5e327e61a91f6cc980f7f8ce754bb4674df88a
Closes-Bug: #1582605

commit_message:
Temporarily support two INTERFACE_DRIVER_OPTS

INTERFACE_DRIVER_OPTS is being moved out of neutron.agent.common.config
into neutron.conf.agent.common [1]. This patch has neutron-lbaas looking
for the values in the old location, and if they aren't found, gets
them from the new location. This patchset is required for Jenkins+1
in [1].

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/343045/

Change-Id: I00e87e9c6f71a8a59e024a9795c48f7699387d85

commit_message:
Use raw disk format as default when create image with glance v2

Currently in the function of _create_v2, it will use qcow2 as the
default disk format. So if there is no disk format specified before
the hand, e.g. in the scenario of creating image from volume backed
instance via Glance v2, it uses qcow2 as the disk format. But XenAPI
doesn't support this image format, so it will always get a failure.
This commit will change to use the disk_format of 'raw' which is
supported by all hypervisor drivers.

Change-Id: I1ff35c77df9b7eda9b1a2f04b918389df6bfd138
Closes-Bug: #1616938

commit_message:
Use ovs_port_updated event to update ofport and mac

Currently, df apps use ovs idl to query the mac of ovs Interface.
ovs_port_updated event was introduced in [1]. And there is already an
ovs Interface object in the event. So, df apps can just get mac address
from that event. This can save a query from ovs db, and also stop abuse
of ovs idl.

[1] 19232467d6ee047c482d384b5c685ad5141184ad

Change-Id: I31d86ce224d43d61cb8861907608248647f10015
Related-Bug: #1622879

commit_message:
Adds tasks so that reverts set objects to ERROR

This patch adds capstone tasks to our flows that make sure reverts
end in the proper final state for the impacted objects.
Previously some failure scenarios left objects in PENDING_* state.

To accomplish the above, this patch adds provisioning status
to all of the remaining top level objects(pools, members, etc.)
and adds tasks to maintain the proper provisioning status for
these objects.

Change-Id: I857b1aa28e4a6c7466c3abf4e088a74367e78faf
Closes-Bug: #1623686

commit_message:
Create v3 API Reference

The Cinder v3 API was marked CURRENT in Mitaka, but there no API ref
was ever created.  This is problematic for end users and would hinder
the v3 API from being included in DefCore Interoperability Guidelines
somewhere down the line (since one of DefCore's Criteria[1] is that a
Capability be well documented).  This patch creates an API ref for v3.
It also adds a header to the v2 index to show that it is SUPPORTED,
whereas v3 is CURRENT.

[1]
http://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack/defcore/tree/doc/source/process/CoreCriteria.rst#n77

Change-Id: Ia3a8050cd04ad3a487a79d80acf9691feee6182e
Closes-Bug: #1616072

Per the HTTP spec
(https://www.w3.org/Protocols/rfc2616/rfc2616-sec10.html#sec10.3.5)
http 304 responses should not include entity headers. Proxies (such as
apache) remove these headers (rightfully) and therefore make it
impossible to test behind a proxy.

Change-Id: I2e26c188e723002e8eb058cfb2d881ab858cfaa4
'}]
commit_message:
Remove invalid assertions for 304 resp

Per the HTTP spec
(https://www.w3.org/Protocols/rfc2616/rfc2616-sec10.html#sec10.3.5)
http 304 responses should not include entity headers. Proxies (such as
apache) remove these headers (rightfully) and therefore make it
impossible to test behind a proxy.

Change-Id: I2e26c188e723002e8eb058cfb2d881ab858cfaa4

commit_message:
3PAR Clean up VLUN deletion on detach

This patch fixes an issue where template VLUNs are left
behind during a detach.  This can happen when a volume is
exported via multiple ports to support multipath and at
detach time one of those paths becomes inactive, bad nic,
pulled cable, etc.

The 3PAR inactive VLUNs are actually templates.  When you
delete a template VLUN, all active VLUNs associated with
that template are also removed.  This patch deletes
template VLUNs at detach time.

Change-Id: If34b76e58684138ca2acb8d38587fb30cfbd5909
Closes-Bug: #1582922
(cherry picked from commit 9b24d615cf78ce7e8d5bac714f63845210bce6ba)

commit_message:
Use dictionary literal for dictionary creation

Dictionary creation could be rewritten as a dictionary literal
to save extra spacing used.
for example:

filters = {}
filter['namespace'] = namespace

could be rewritten as

filters = {'namespace': namespace}

These changes are only for test cases.code will be covered in
later patches and correponsing hacking check will be implemented.

Referece: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/210303/
https://review.openstack.org/#/q/topic:dict-cleanup
http://docs.openstack.org/developer/hacking/#dictionaries-lists

Change-Id: Ia6de44145c1b6a9018293dedfdfa1020eb1c2a55

commit_message:
quota-defaults lists info with wrong tenant-id

Only admin can get default quotas after this patch.

Typical exceptions:
1.Http 404 will be returned if admin get a not exist tenant's default
quotas
2.Http 403 will be returned if not admin get other tenant's default quotas.

Change-Id: I586514f67d83b4e0ea49c6883005f438bf09ae28
Closes-Bug:#1307486

commit_message:
Storwize: update the retype after replication v2.1

This patch updates the implemetation of retype and adds the
test cases to cover the retype between a replication type
and non replication type, and remove the stretch cluster
test cases, because they are no longer valid.

Change-Id: I686708287d68bc4d6fd28c341031163750d4c1c1
Closes-Bug: #1560632

commit_message:
Fujitsu DX: Add retry to save some failure

Adds retry to save failure by busy error or connection error.
The following messages are error examples:
(1) cannot connect to ETERNUS
(2) 32786, The Logical Volume is in busy state
(3) 32787, The device is in busy state

Change-Id: I969b7a42fec5507290f4599cda4aac67bc66553e
Closes-Bug: #1560953

commit_message:
Add missing glance_metadata field to Snapshot

Snapshot object was missing glance_metadata field that should be
defined in the SQLAlchemy model and oslo versioned object.
This commit adds this missing field.

Partial-Bug: 1509012
Change-Id: I2bb3224fee70f9763962992219961396b6834130

commit_message:
Remove exception when doing 1st incremental backup

The exception will stop users to do an incremental
backup for the first backup. It makes the user
experience more friendly if the exception is
removed.

Change-Id: I17ad92fcd530a357bb6b8e4184b288a32d548801
Closes-Bug: #1536654

commit_message:
Move DB-related tests from unit to funcitonal

In general, unit-tests should not use DB. So this patch
moves DB API and DB migrations tests to functional.

commit_message:
Clean up the prior implementation of replication

Since the replication v2.1 has been implemented, the old implementation
of replication v2.0 and before should be erased from the code.

However, the code related to replication_driver_data and
replication_extended_status are left untouched, since it has got
a lot of code from different drivers involved and it needs to
reach an agreement with different drivers.

Change-Id: I923edc49827de8e6dd0fe193c1b6d830dedb567f
Closes-Bug: #1560643

commit_message:
Hitachi: extend volume if larger than snapshot

Extend volume if during create_volume_from_snapshot() the new volume
is larger than the snapshot it was created from. Extended test case to
cover the change, fixed some error tests to reflect the change.

Closes-Bug: #1560652
Closes-Bug: #1560653

commit_message:
Fix infortrend driver bug: cloned with src vol size

It's possible to create a volume from a source volume with
a larger size. However, infortrend driver does not extend
the volume when clone has finished. This patch fixes it.

Change-Id: I413efb6a998ec0db5ac42fdd6dd69a82bc260e3d
Closes-Bug: #1554784

cover the change.

commit_message:
Xio driver doesn't honor create from snapshot volume size

Create_volume_from_snapshot can specify a volume size larger than
the orginal snapshot. Xio driver not appear to handle this size
difference. This patch fixes it.

Change-Id: I2d73e28bca306f5a4d66c53c874c933af04562a4
Closes-Bug: #1560641

subject: Fix log statement logged twice
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-07-07 08:55:00.000000000', 'files': ['cinderclient/shell.py', 'cinderclient/api_versions.py'], 'message': 'Fix log statement logged twice

Log statemet is logged twice for SessionClient or HTTPClient because
logging.basicConfig() call is adding StreamHandler to root logger and
as propagate attribute of logger object is by default True the log
messgae will also be logged by the handlers of the ancestors loggers.

For a fix, removed logging.basicConfig() call.

Change-Id: I3b06319c446815d5c531dbb90c19732e489ffcd5
Closes-Bug: #1572844
'}]
commit_message:
Fix log statement logged twice

Log statemet is logged twice for SessionClient or HTTPClient because
logging.basicConfig() call is adding StreamHandler to root logger and
as propagate attribute of logger object is by default True the log
messgae will also be logged by the handlers of the ancestors loggers.

For a fix, removed logging.basicConfig() call.

Change-Id: I3b06319c446815d5c531dbb90c19732e489ffcd5
Closes-Bug: #1572844

commit_message:
Move fake_constants to root test directory

The fake_constants module is used across unit and
functional tests, and likely in the future will be
used for more tests.  Given that the fakes are intended
to be generally used and available for all test types
they should be located in the root tests directory.

This is a minor thing, but it clearly indicates that they
are available and usable for all of the various test types
that are implemented.

Change-Id: Id12b9400198278cac70217a95b5d9f7a9240be9d

commit_message:
Add the upper constraints to package versions

Currently tox does not have any upper constraints, due to which there is a
possibility of tox to use a newer version of dependent library that may not
be supported yet. This patch add the upper constrainsts as set by the
openstack/requirements repository

Change-Id: Ib50c3b7676a990261e0c0aea87d7dfc23bbcb415

commit_message:
Smbfs volume driver should use DLM

In attempt to make Cinder HA A/A ready SmbfsDriver and
WindowsSmbfsDriver should start using
RemoteFSSnapDriverDistributed instead of RemoteFSSnapDriver,
this will change locked snapshot operations to use distributed
lock manager.
Moreover remotefs.locked_volume_id_operation decorator should
be switched to coordination.synchronized.

Partially implements: blueprint cinder-volume-active-active-support
Closes-bug: 1607074

Change-Id: I934a9c5ba3cf314587fb222fe28f3d13f08dff35

commit_message:
Reduced the complexity of the send_cmd method (in ProphetStor)

The get_events method is very large - almost 140 lines,
and McCabe's cyclomatic complexity 35.
(in cinder/volume/drivers/prophetstor/dplcommon.py)
I extracted some of the functionalities into helper functions
to reduce the length and complexity of send_cmd.
Additionally it became more readable as well, without
changing its functionality.

Change-Id: Ifca22b35b1aea90bcc2a04ab5d81c178a83d6bc6

commit_message:
Add the upper constraints to package versions

Currently tox does not have any upper constraints, due to which there is a
possibility of tox to use a newer version of dependent library that may not
be supported yet. This patch add the upper constrainsts as set by the
openstack/requirements repository

Change-Id: Ie69fafc7e10f592f8b3f62019831d1909da2d818

[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-07-05 09:29:34.000000000', 'files': ['cinder/volume/drivers/ibm/flashsystem_common.py', 'cinder/volume/drivers/ibm/flashsystem_iscsi.py', 'cinder/volume/drivers/ibm/flashsystem_fc.py', 'cinder/tests/unit/test_ibm_flashsystem.py', 'cinder/tests/unit/test_ibm_flashsystem_iscsi.py'], 'message': 'FlashSystem: Create lager volume from vol/snap

If the destination volume have a size larger then the source volume or
snapshot base volume size, in flashsystem_common
create_volume_from_snapshot() will raise exception "Volume size is
different from snapshot based volume." and in flashsystem_common
create_cloned_volume() will raise exception "Source and destination
size differ." Thus, the volume creation will fail.

In this fix,
* Add support to create volume with lager size from volume.
* Add support to create volume with lager size from snapshot.
* Get volume size directly from backend in extend_volume().
* Bump version to 1.0.12.

Change-Id: I44ad3ebd93d2b9c1cb2871d0b1add01b6173612b
Close-bug: #1598688
'}]
commit_message:
FlashSystem: Create lager volume from vol/snap

If the destination volume have a size larger then the source volume or
snapshot base volume size, in flashsystem_common
create_volume_from_snapshot() will raise exception "Volume size is
different from snapshot based volume." and in flashsystem_common
create_cloned_volume() will raise exception "Source and destination
size differ." Thus, the volume creation will fail.

In this fix,
* Add support to create volume with lager size from volume.
* Add support to create volume with lager size from snapshot.
* Get volume size directly from backend in extend_volume().
* Bump version to 1.0.12.

Change-Id: I44ad3ebd93d2b9c1cb2871d0b1add01b6173612b
Close-bug: #1598688

commit_message:
Fix connecting unnecessary iSCSI sessions issue

There are two types of iSCSI multipath devices.

 type1) shares the same iqn between multiple portals.
 type2) used ifferent iqns on different portals.

In case of type1, client can found out which
target is correct by iqn stored in iscsi_properties,
so it's unnecessary to connect to all of the targets
which discovered.

Closes-Bug: #1562665
Change-Id: Iaf8617e432241400e492b4d3ec46c90f7ddd8ee6

commit_message:
Set QoS on cloned volumes

Not sure where/when it happened yet, but it looks like the QoS setting for
clone volume has been dropped.

This patch fixes it back up by checking the new volumes type info for
QoS settings after clone.

Change-Id: I48a3d0e5f15417235a2041535c0c671fbaafb0a8
Closes-Bug: #1589187
(cherry picked from commit f57447223a359d64f47795d9ff57a68a8481c0ed)

commit_message:
Refactor create, save, and destroy OVO methods

As we go adding more and more OVOs it becomes clear that we have quite a
lot of code duplication, and this patch tries to address some of those
cases.

This patch creates default create, save, and destroy methods in
CinderPersistentObject removing duplicated code and reducing code
required for new OVOs, as only code for special cases will be required.

As a side effect of the refactoring we get a small speed improvement on
get_by_id method on the first call of each OVO.

Change-Id: I7de0e435e4bc5ef040d1209762b816c61330c76e

The resource_type must be a dictionary rather than None
when volume_type is None. Because the None can not use
the method of 'get' to get the value of extra_specs.

ref: https://github.com/openstack/cinder/blob/master/cinder/scheduler/filters/capabilities_filter.py#L34
extra_specs = resource_type.get('extra_specs', [])

Change-Id: Ica995748fb22e89ab28641e99af087e220597d9d
Closes-Bug: #1557837
"}]
commit_message:
The resource_type must be a dictionary

The resource_type must be a dictionary rather than None
when volume_type is None. Because the None can not use
the method of 'get' to get the value of extra_specs.

ref: https://github.com/openstack/cinder/blob/master/cinder/scheduler/filters/capabilities_filter.py#L34
extra_specs = resource_type.get('extra_specs', [])

Change-Id: Ica995748fb22e89ab28641e99af087e220597d9d
Closes-Bug: #1557837

[{'number': 7, 'created': '2016-05-31 01:31:20.000000000', 'files': ['cinder/backup/manager.py', 'cinder/tests/unit/backup/test_backup.py'], 'message': 'Update the status of backup-restore

During the process of backup restore, we may not just set the
status of the volume to "error", for we could not know whether
it is "volume_create error" or "backup_restore error". Also, for
us, the "error_restoring" status is one of the "error" status, but
can help to distinguish the reason of error.

Change-Id: I6145cf7793ff77af05670fb0e8c411d9f3711526
'}]
commit_message:
Update the status of backup-restore

During the process of backup restore, we may not just set the
status of the volume to "error", for we could not know whether
it is "volume_create error" or "backup_restore error". Also, for
us, the "error_restoring" status is one of the "error" status, but
can help to distinguish the reason of error.

Change-Id: I6145cf7793ff77af05670fb0e8c411d9f3711526

commit_message:
Standardize on raising webob exceptions

Currently there is a mix of 'raise'ing and 'return'ing webob exceptions.
Assuming there is no difference in behaviour, it may make sense to
standardize on 'raise'ing these exceptions.

Change-Id: Ia329fa4685aa860763628ef6d8fe780650d009a6
Closes-bug: 1563303

commit_message:
Disable queuing on multipath device before flushing it

If queuing is enabled on multipath, queuing needs to be disabled before
attempting to flush the device else it will fail. It is a no-op
if queuing is disabled

Closes-Bug: 1592520
Change-Id: I22ca3c98534bacdc57c76dbc7b1e17d547117deb

commit_message:
Catch db exception when create volume

Creating volume from image.Cinder canâ€™t catch the exception from
the db .That will reschedule to create volume twice and raise
ImageExists.this patch is to catch the exception.

Closes-Bug: #1521083

Change-Id: Ida2866489609f758dd99faa1fd7c10b618382b23

commit_message:
Let /types API list all volume types by default

Currently, if admin user wants to list all volume types,
he had to specify a weird option to /types API
as follows:
/types?is_public=None

It's not easy to understand by end user, so we'd
better to let /types list all public and non-public
types while is_public option is not specified.
And let /types?is_public=False return all non-public ones,
/types?is_public=True list all public ones.

APIImpact

Change-Id: Ibd259ea7d40cf6ed52a2e55d073d821df2dcef13

commit_message:
Add hacking for assertFalse

Unit tests should use assertFalse(value) instead of using
assertEqual(False, value).
For example:assertEqual(a,False) is equal to assertFalse(a)

Change-Id: Ibae94940d5d28c468bf4632ae6ba454ed32a125c

commit_message:
Improve the retrieval feature of message

Currently the error message can only be retrieved by
message id. This patch tries to improve it so that
the message can be get by the resource uuid.

Change-Id: I4e15ede99c3f65ebdf43fa8616e5d49ac171fa15
Implements: blueprint summarymessage

commit_message:
Multipath: fix race when detaching devices

'multipath -f' can be racy and multipath/udev is not happy about that,
causing systemd-udevd to enter D-state.
This patch retries a flush operation if it flush failed with
exit 1. This is a condition identified and reported in RHBZ
https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1368211. A one-second
sleep is enough to overcome this issue. The one-second sleep is only
triggered _IF_ the exit is 1. Otherwise, raise a flush error and do
not try to attempt the underlying LUN removal, in order to avoid
lingering D-state LUNs, which can only be removed upon a entire
compute reboot.

Change-Id: I08363cdbaa62bc1b10b67d0ab0eb6b57ea836959
Closes-Bug: 1592520
Signed-off-by: Rodrigo Freire <rbs@brasilia.br>

The os_brick project does not have configuration options, so this
approach is required to get cluster configuration settings into the
connector.

When using ironic virt driver, if scheduled_node is not specified
in rebuild_instance compute manager method (as it happens in case
of instance rebuild), the first ironic node is selected:

 computes = ComputeNodeList.get_all_by_host(context, host, use_slave)

After the first rebuild, instance.node is updated to be this first

commit_message:
Update instance node on rebuild only when it is recreate

When using ironic virt driver, if scheduled_node is not specified
in rebuild_instance compute manager method (as it happens in case
of instance rebuild), the first ironic node is selected:

 computes = ComputeNodeList.get_all_by_host(context, host, use_slave)
 return computes[0]

After the first rebuild, instance.node is updated to be this first
ironic node, which causes subsequent rebuilds to fail, as virt driver
tries to set instance_uuid on a newly selected ironic node and fails.

Closes-bug: #1564921
Change-Id: I2fe6e439135ba6aa4120735d030ced31081ef202

commit_message:
Update cp line to remove redundant param

The use of -r for cp command is redundant with -a being used as
documentation on Linux has -R and -r as the same parameter. The
issue on Mac OS X is that it will error on about using -R and -r
with cp. Change removes redundant -r from cp command.

Change-Id: If7122efc8b84f8aa8a07fe4f8ee7568a048c9461

commit_message:
incorrect use CONF.set_override

In the file freezer/common/config.py, the function CONF.set_override
was used with error parameter as follow.
CONF.set_override('log_file', defaults['log_file'], levels.get(
                   log.NOTSET))

CONF.set_override function prototype:
set_override(self, name, override, group=None, enforce_type=False)

The third parameter is invalid. It should be removed.

Change-Id: Ia18040585e18d9ea35aa829c80ab487eb8a98d04
Closes-Bug: #1621770

commit_message:
Avoid circular refs more aggressively in DependencyTaskGroup

Be ultra-careful to make sure that we can't end up with a local reference
to a traceback that contains the current function, thus causing a reference
loop where everything on the call stack has to be garbage collected.

Also, ignore exceptions from cancelling threads in _cancel_recursively(),
just as we do in cancel_all() since
2ffbd913a647cd1c8d5e1d85c29f104a5a4a326e.

Change-Id: I635c41faab4b54e95132a93f8046d0a63053485d
Related-Bug: #1626675

commit_message:
cp -ar breaks some platforms

cp -ar is redundant. cp -a implies -r so the -r is not needed. And
unfortunately on MacOSX you cannot specify both parameters or it will
fail breaking running local tests.

commit_message:
Add missing slash to dir path

When validating a PF in the method 'get_function_by_ifname'

commit_message:
Update trunk metadata during wire/unwire operations

Before this patch metadata on the OVS trunk bridge were
not updated during unwiring operations and upon subsequent
wire operations old subports were getting wiped from the
external_ids field of the OVS parent port. This could lead
to OVS ports left behind on the host on trunk removal.

This patch ensures that the subports stored as metadata
reflect the logical state of the trunk.

Closes-bug: #1625875

Change-Id: I9d885b10d84fad43c527d3ca7bc9a37439197fc9
(cherry picked from commit 29457631ad0b77b06dee40cb5114f5f4aced129a)

commit_message:
Ensure trunk status is acknowledged during OVS subport operations

Before this patch, change to trunk status was reported only when
subports were being added, but not when being removed. This patch
tweak things to make sure the same happens on subports removal.

This patch also improves unit coverage for the parts of the code
affected. In particular the import of oslo_context has been aliased
to catch errors where context as variable is shadowed by the homonym
module.

Closes-bug: #1625135

Change-Id: I73127d7829c31ca66578eb8f7d76409b36c9dc6d
(cherry picked from commit 4371ae010a7888220bb67ca9bd423e54c0239fd4)

commit_message:
Fix dhcp_release6 error when not supported

If the system does not have a version of dnsmasq that supports
dhcp_release6, warn about but otherwise handle it gracefully, and also
don't even try to execute it the next time.

Closes-Bug: #1622002
Related-Bug: #1624079

(cherry picked from commit d4f92ede9ed52cd0b9059d993e3cf1f42d5ff57e)

dhcp_release6, warn about but otherwise handle it gracefully, and also
don't even try to execute it the next time.

Related-Bug: #1624079

commit_message:
Modify api startup parameters in devstack plugin

Because the api binary script is generated by pbr now, the api
startup parameters need to be adapted accordingly in devstack
script or the api will be unable to start if the devstack deploy
mode is 'simple'.

Change-Id: I72abc3a83a4a2cf993198b0b1ac98c79ee26ec56
Closes-Bug: #1626979

Was looking for the original volume and sc server object
after the primary was down. We now look for the new primary

commit_message:
Dell SC: Error attaching after LV-AFO

Fixed miscellaneous errors dealing with the state of Dell's
Live Volumes after a LV AFO event.

Was looking for the original volume and sc server object
after the primary was down. We now look for the new primary
and attach that.

Ensure export was failing to properly kick off a swap
back to the original primary if it was available.

Fixed an error with deleting replications.

Added a workaround to finding a ScLiveVolume object. Previous
method could return stale information.

Change-Id: I58889adbcf279d4b0107cbc51e1dace888a3fb15
Closes-Bug: #1617401

commit_message:
Fix creating typeless volumes with Mitaka's c-sch

In Mitaka as a workaround for creating volumes without volume type c-api
was sending an empty dictionary as request_spec['volume_type'] in
create_volume() RPC cast to scheduler. This changed in Newton and we're
handling this situation directly in scheduler, but when running Newton's
c-api with Mitaka's c-sch we should mimic older behavior. This patch
implements that.

Change-Id: I3dbb1934f3d8e68fef49f56155cbf59bc5fadc3a
Closes-Bug: 1619008
(cherry picked from commit 91bdf9de4c1e0726892384605704d87b318e7a69)

commit_message:
Using assertIsNone() instead of assertIs(None, ..)

Following OpenStack Style Guidelines[1]:
http://docs.openstack.org/developer/hacking/#unit-tests-and-assertraises
[H203] Unit test assertions tend to give better messages for more
specific assertions. As a result, assertIsNone(...) is preferred
over assertEqual(None, ...) and assertIs(..,None)

Change-Id: Id79b00971f993298013aa6545a797543ee1c54fb

[{'number': 6, 'created': '2016-09-23 21:28:59.000000000', 'files': ['networking_odl/ml2/mech_driver.py', 'networking_odl/tests/unit/common/test_filters.py', 'networking_odl/common/filters.py'], 'message': 'security group rule: convert unknown protocol name

Neutron security group API accepts name or integer as protocol.
e.g. "tcp" or "6"
Neutron keeps adding protocol names for more human readability.
It's, however, troublesome for OpenDaylight to catch up those protocol
names. So networking-odl should convert protocol name unknown to
OpenDaylight to integer because this conversion can be easily done
in neutron. It's because neutron already knows it.
Although it's possible to always convert protocol name to integer,
this isn't done because of compatibility.

commit_message:
security group rule: convert unknown protocol name

Neutron security group API accepts name or integer as protocol.
e.g. "tcp" or "6"
Neutron keeps adding protocol names for more human readability.
It's, however, troublesome for OpenDaylight to catch up those protocol
names. So networking-odl should convert protocol name unknown to
OpenDaylight to integer because this conversion can be easily done
in neutron. It's because neutron already knows it.
Although it's possible to always convert protocol name to integer,
this isn't done because of compatibility.

This depends on OpenDaylight patch which was already merged.
https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/#/c/35836/

Change-Id: I50a5678d4adbab7ecc5de7a9616612404644de54

commit_message:
Fix the belongsTo query parameter

The belongsTo query parameter is only supported by the v2.0
token validation API. It would check the ID of the project passed
to the belongsTo parameter against the project a token was scoped to.

This commit corrects the implementation, tests, and adds
documentation. It also moves the check to keystone.token.controller
since belongsTo is a v2-ism and doesn't belong in the
keystone.token.provider.

Closes-Bug: 1627085
Closes-Bug: 1626794
Change-Id: I4a06a498112b81093d7e5ef3142bb1e2d0f78138

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-09-22 13:02:27.000000000', 'files': ['nova/tests/unit/test_nova_manage.py'], 'message': 'Standardize output capture for nova-manage tests

The nova-manage tests used a large mix of output capture
techniques. monkey patching sys.stdout inside a test. Doing a direct
symbol replace of sys.stdout. Sometimes doing nothing, which meant the
output was going all the way to the test buffer.

This standardizes a model of doing creating a self.output during class
setup where output is expected, which is fixture monkey patched to
replace sys.stdout. It brings some consistency to the output handling,
as well as removes a large number of leaked through stdout lines that
were confusing in the test output stream.

Change-Id: Iff630e74bb86349c9ed9ae6b85c177948710f7c1
'}]
commit_message:
Standardize output capture for nova-manage tests

The nova-manage tests used a large mix of output capture
techniques. monkey patching sys.stdout inside a test. Doing a direct
symbol replace of sys.stdout. Sometimes doing nothing, which meant the
output was going all the way to the test buffer.

This standardizes a model of doing creating a self.output during class
setup where output is expected, which is fixture monkey patched to
replace sys.stdout. It brings some consistency to the output handling,
as well as removes a large number of leaked through stdout lines that
were confusing in the test output stream.

Change-Id: Iff630e74bb86349c9ed9ae6b85c177948710f7c1

commit_message:
Work around tests that don't use nova.test as a base

The db migration tests use a bunch of setup inside oslo_db that is
only exported as a base test class. This means that none of these do
the standard setup that the rest of the Nova tests do, including
things like logging capture.

Long term, the relationship between nova and oslo_db needs to be fixed
so that these are available as fixtures, not just base class. However,
in the short term we can setup logging correctly before initializing
the rest of the test class to keep these from scrambling the test
output.

Change-Id: I3c663d276cffa6146ac8f45bde7d70f7aece0c89

commit_message:
Add logging to NumaTopology Filter

The NumaTopology Filter does not currently report the reason for a
node being excluded. It would be useful to have some logging to
indicate the filters assessment of the resources available on a
compute node and the resources requested for the instance so that
we can identify the reason why the instance can't be scheduled.
This will be useful when assessing bugs that assert that an instance
has been incorrectly rejected.

Change-Id: I8330e6e711ad9dd9676388e094be80683856e6b0

revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-09-22 12:32:13.000000000', 'files': ['nova/tests/unit/test_hacking.py'], 'message': "Don't print to stdout when executing hacking checks

The way the hacking tests _run_check works, it ends up evaluating
python code in a context where all of our stdout capture has been
undone. The pep8 check_all method *also* prints out the errors found,
not only accumulating them for later. We can patch out the method
doing that to keep this from leaking through the test output, which
only causes confusion.

Change-Id: I9be4801352c4977504d95123d01bcbe309f22347
"}]
commit_message:
Don't print to stdout when executing hacking checks

The way the hacking tests _run_check works, it ends up evaluating
python code in a context where all of our stdout capture has been
undone. The pep8 check_all method *also* prints out the errors found,
not only accumulating them for later. We can patch out the method
doing that to keep this from leaking through the test output, which
only causes confusion.

Change-Id: I9be4801352c4977504d95123d01bcbe309f22347

commit_message:
Make test logging setup fixture disable future setup

Our logging fixture sets up logging in a way that we need to capture
things during tests. However, some of our tests do things like call
back into main functions, which then call logging setup again, and
unwind everything we're doing (including debug message testing).

This patches out oslo_log setup after the fixture runs, thus ignoring
calls to it in the future. It removes a couple of scary looking stack
traces from the test stream that shouldn't be there.

Change-Id: Ie1b7d4370f20597961a841c5bc0a1ad7cc42b2ef

commit_message:
Fix Mariadb restarting issue

Mariadb fails with the below error

"160608 12:46:16 [ERROR] Found 1 prepared transactions!
It means that mysqld was not shut down properly last time and
critical recovery information (last binlog or tc.log file) was manually
deleted after a crash.
You have to start mysqld with --tc-heuristic-recover switch to
commit or rollback pending transactions."

I have tried with both option and in my case "commit" works.

Change-Id: I7c19f67a2a95ab07926076466c601ec9d2aa9a73
Closes-Bug: #1590639

commit_message:
conf: Add 'deprecated_reason' to osapi opts

This is the standardized way of explaining why an option was removed.
The 'deprecated_group' arguments are also removed as they name the same
group that the option is currently in thus making them superfluous.

Change-Id: I3040441470f0e2f2e53d26b980a0b6a48e41b1ea
Implements: blueprint centralize-config-options-ocata

[H203] Unit test assertions tend to give better messages for more specific assertions.

commit_message:
Using assertIsNone() instead of assertEqual(None)

Following OpenStack Style Guidelines[1]:
http://docs.openstack.org/developer/hacking/#unit-tests-and-assertraises
[H203] Unit test assertions tend to give better messages for more specific assertions.
As a result, assertIsNone(...) is preferred over assertEqual(None, ...) and assertIs(..,None)

Change-Id: I8881abed6e7962d1516323725e194937bce1346f

commit_message:
Orphan view and multipath issue in Kaminario driver

"create_volume_from_snapshot" method leaves an orphan view in Kaminario
K2 iSCSI and FC Cinder Drivers. "create_volume_from_snapshot" and
"create_cloned_volume" methods are not removing multipath_devices while
detaching temporary attached volume/view for copying data.

Change-Id: I3f064777ce0dd4264c3682f5724b3bb46f282311
Closes-Bug: #1620781
Co-Authored-By: Lakshman<Lakshmi.Narayana.ctr@kaminario.com>

commit_message:
Bump openstacksdk minimum requirement to 0.9.7

OpenStackClient requires an openstacksdk minimum requirement of
0.9.6 for new network commands and features. However, version
0.9.6 has a known issue for senlin. This patch bumps the mimimum
version to 0.9.7 to address both needs.

Change-Id: I2ad67cdbfa3bbf438c9b3321487111e3e80344c3

commit_message:
move os_vif.initialize() to nova-compute start

os_vif.initialize() was previously executed during module load. This
means it was entirely possible that it was run before things like
logging were actually set up in the expected way. Move this back into
execution time instead of load time to ensure that logging is actually
setup.

Changes need to be made to tests which make assumptions about os_vif
objects to manually initialize os_vif when it will be used. os_vif
objects can't be created until it is initialized, so some delayed
object creation is also done in test_vif.py.

Closes-Bug: #1615676

Change-Id: I89fe5c5b3d762f3a3238b587685df85d15ee56c4

[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-09-21 16:13:42.000000000', 'files': ['nova/tests/functional/api/openstack/placement/fixtures.py'], 'message': '[placement] Manage log and other output in gabbi fixure

Recent changes to the placement API added more verbose logging and
output across both stdout and stderr. In test runs this resulted in
a combination of far too much output as well as output that was
impossible to read because it was interleaved.

This change uses fixtures from nova.tests.fixtures to capture
stray output streams and logs.

It also adds a specific logger for the ERROR level that overrides
the fixture log handling to send that level to the default stderr.
This is required in order to effectively see error messages on both
side of the wsgi-intercept used when running gabbi. Without this,
the errors are swallowed and test development and debugging,
especially locally for TDD, is hamstrung.

Closes-Bug: #1623573
Change-Id: I300456b0261dfc0ae46c799e5a03cbeab25106c2
'}]
commit_message:
[placement] Manage log and other output in gabbi fixure

Recent changes to the placement API added more verbose logging and
output across both stdout and stderr. In test runs this resulted in
a combination of far too much output as well as output that was
impossible to read because it was interleaved.

This change uses fixtures from nova.tests.fixtures to capture
stray output streams and logs.

It also adds a specific logger for the ERROR level that overrides
the fixture log handling to send that level to the default stderr.
This is required in order to effectively see error messages on both
side of the wsgi-intercept used when running gabbi. Without this,
the errors are swallowed and test development and debugging,
especially locally for TDD, is hamstrung.

Closes-Bug: #1623573
Change-Id: I300456b0261dfc0ae46c799e5a03cbeab25106c2

commit_message:
Bump tenacity to 3.1.1

We are replacing all usages of the 'retrying' package with
'tenacity' as the author of retrying is not actively maintaining
the project. Tenacity is a fork of retrying, but has improved the
interface and extensibility (see [1] for more details). Our end
goal here is removing the retrying package from our requirements.

While working through the replacement of retrying with
tenacity [3] we uncovered a critical bug in tenacity that
was fixed with [4]. This fix has been release as part of
tenacity 3.1.1 [2].

This patch bumps our version of tenacity to 3.1.1 in order
to pickup the fix in [4].

[1] https://github.com/jd/tenacity
[2] https://pypi.python.org/pypi/tenacity/3.1.1
[3] https://review.openstack.org/#/q/topic:retrying-to-tenacity
[4] https://github.com/jd/tenacity/pull/28

Change-Id: I8ff3333401e9c3a732076a365acae89ad8feeb47

commit_message:
Fix unset commands to pass normally when nothing specified

After I found this problem appear in "volume unset",
I checked all the volume command and also found some
same problems. This patch fix them all.
The main reason of we ignored this problem before is
there was not any tests for it. So I add tests for
"nothing unset" for them all to test and aviod this
problem.
Also, I add unit tests for all snapshot commands
in volume v1 by the way in this patch. We will
need more tests to avoid some ignored problem.

Change-Id: I46775f24643d715e168b30785b8b531c0431a55b
Partial-bug: #1588588

commit_message:
Add devstack plugin support for fwaas v2

This sets up a new devstack keyword - q-fwaas-v1 - in addition to the
existing q-fwaas plugin.  The q-fwaas keyword configures the devstack
plugin to support FWaaS v2.  FWaaS v2 is the future, and should be the
default for development at this point.  But the new keyword, q-fwaas-v1,
will set things up for FWaaS v1, and there is also q-fwaas-v2 to
explicitly select FWaaS v2.

Also ensure that /etc/neutron/policy.d gets set up for FWaaS
policy.json.

Depends-On: I88be1670a42fcca4aba3b643a1c5a072ce0d1035
Needed-By: I07a4e5a54c0ad862de791b655445e01f805981e4
Change-Id: If35ca26028ddedcf1bc22dd8749cb11c69a1ccbb

commit_message:
Workaround DHCP agent gate issues

The DHCP agent logs in the gate-tempest-dsvm-networking-ovn job
see numerous key errors as reported in bug 1624079. These errors
appear to be related to setting the DHCP agent force_metadata
or enable_isolated_metadata configuration options to True.

These key errors may be related to the recent instability of the
gate-tempest-dsvm-networking-ovn job. While bug 1624079 is being
fixed, we will only force the DHCP agent to handle metadata when
native OVN L3 is enabled.

Change-Id: Iaa13240150dcf7541e4b2adfb9112cf9d006442b
Related-Bug: 1624079

Align puppet-tripleo with other Puppet OpenStack modules to use
puppet-openstack_spec_helper.

Here are the benefits:

- Allow to use Depends-On between Puppet OpenStack modules and
  puppet-tripleo, and unit tests will work correctly with dependencies.
- Use the Puppet OpenStack gemspec file that handle gems dependencies to
  test the module.
- Allow to re-use ruby helper that Puppet OpenStack modules have in unit
  tests, to avoid duplicated code.
- Don't manage .fixtures.yml file, it will be generated by Puppet

Change-Id: Ic66e9f872c57545327a9fb4b8ae86fbf0abbd8be
"}]
commit_message:
Switch puppet-tripleo to use puppet-openstack_spec_helper

Align puppet-tripleo with other Puppet OpenStack modules to use
puppet-openstack_spec_helper.

Here are the benefits:

- Allow to use Depends-On between Puppet OpenStack modules and
  puppet-tripleo, and unit tests will work correctly with dependencies.
- Use the Puppet OpenStack gemspec file that handle gems dependencies to
  test the module.
- Allow to re-use ruby helper that Puppet OpenStack modules have in unit
  tests, to avoid duplicated code.
- Don't manage .fixtures.yml file, it will be generated by Puppet
  OpenStack tooling. TripleO dependencies will live in Puppetfile_extras.

Change-Id: Ic66e9f872c57545327a9fb4b8ae86fbf0abbd8be

subject: Fix the broken UT of huawei driver for py34/35
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-09-23 18:37:07.000000000', 'files': ['manila/tests/share/drivers/huawei/test_huawei_nas.py'], 'message': 'Fix the broken UT of huawei driver for py34/35

The cause of failing unit tests is a bug in huawei driver.
When huawei driver logins to backend, it reads username/password from
huawei configuration file. If the username/password are configured as
plain text, huawei driver'll encode them and overwrite the encoded text
to the configuration file.

The encoding logic code is like this:
  six.text_type(base64.b64encode("***"))

For py27, this code works fine. However, for py34, this text_type
converting adds some extra words to result unicode string, like
"b'***'"('***' is the actual encoded result string).
Once driver reads the username/password again, it'll get the incorrect
text and then fail while jsonutils.dumps.

All the failed unit tests tried to call login twice, and triggered the
error condition said above.

This patch is just a workaround, because those failed tests actually
no need to login twice, the redundant login calls are removed.

Another patch will be commited to fix the problem thoroughly in huawei
driver.  Bug https://launchpad.net/bugs/1612149 has been raised for
that work, and will also analyze what changed to trigger this issue
only recently.

Change-Id: Ia6bf7bbb9ffb9644085bbdf4f5576f09215a877f
Closes-Bug: #1612149
(cherry picked from commit 5ea4911794df4a744afe825e6083b82549a5f384)
'}]
commit_message:
Fix the broken UT of huawei driver for py34/35

The cause of failing unit tests is a bug in huawei driver.
When huawei driver logins to backend, it reads username/password from
huawei configuration file. If the username/password are configured as
plain text, huawei driver'll encode them and overwrite the encoded text
to the configuration file.

The encoding logic code is like this:
  six.text_type(base64.b64encode("***"))

For py27, this code works fine. However, for py34, this text_type
converting adds some extra words to result unicode string, like
"b'***'"('***' is the actual encoded result string).
Once driver reads the username/password again, it'll get the incorrect
text and then fail while jsonutils.dumps.

All the failed unit tests tried to call login twice, and triggered the
error condition said above.

This patch is just a workaround, because those failed tests actually
no need to login twice, the redundant login calls are removed.

Another patch will be commited to fix the problem thoroughly in huawei
driver.  Bug https://launchpad.net/bugs/1612149 has been raised for
that work, and will also analyze what changed to trigger this issue
only recently.

Change-Id: Ia6bf7bbb9ffb9644085bbdf4f5576f09215a877f
Closes-Bug: #1612149
(cherry picked from commit 5ea4911794df4a744afe825e6083b82549a5f384)

commit_message:
Deployment should fail when trying to add another Ceph cluster's OSD

This change explicitly adds the FSID to the $cluster_option variable
and causes Puppet to exit if OSD preparation/activation will fail
because the OSD belongs to a different Ceph cluster as determined by
an FSID mismatch. FSID mismatch is a symptom of attempting to install
over another deploy. The FSID mismatch failure will be logged so that
the user may determine the reason for failure and then choose to zap
away the old deploy away before re-attempting deployment.

Closes-Bug: 1604728
Change-Id: I61d18400754842860372c4cc5f3b80d104d59706

commit_message:
Add in rspec-puppet-facts support

This change pulls in rspec-puppet-facts to provide the basic default
facts for puppet-tripleo rspec tests. rspec-puppet-facts provides an
easy to use interface to allow for the same set of tests to be executed
with multiple sets of operating system facts. In most cases this
includes defaults for Debian/RedHat based systems. In puppet-tripleo's
case this is just RHEL/CentOS. We are removing the Fedora listing from
the metadata.json as we only support RHEL and CentOS for tripleo.
This change also updates the existing rspec tests to leverage
rspec-puppet-facts to be more consistent with how facts are defined.

Change-Id: I0ddc71799d74ee95b9828aea6a8dcb4abb4e4e62

commit_message:
Implement pre_upgrade hook when deploying undercloud

This patch adds a new option in undercloud.conf: pre_upgrade.

If set to True (default so our users can upgrade undercloud it out of the box),
it will run some actions required to before Puppet run.
Those actions are now:
- stop openstack-* services
- stop neutron-* services
They are required now because otherwise Puppet catalog will hang on
restarting services later during the upgrade process.
Instead of doing it in tripleoclient, let's do it here.

Change-Id: I3903a6c14659048254061dee8fb0575434a344a4

commit_message:
Create os_workers fact

This change adds a new fact that can be used as the default values for
any worker configuration. When used this fact will reduce the number of
default workers configured for services. Previously we were using
$::processorcount which could lead to excessive memory consumption or
connection limits being execeeded when services were deployed on
baremetal with large number of processors. The os_workers fact uses the
larger of two following values, '2' or '# processors / 4' but will not
exceed '8'.

Change-Id: Ia588817fde9203a134bc9eaad9a5bd5453d7639a

commit_message:
Ensure trunk status is acknowledged during OVS subport operations

Before this patch, change to trunk status was reported only when
subports were being added, but not when being removed. This patch
tweak things to make sure the same happens on subports removal.

This patch also improves unit coverage for the parts of the code
affected. In particular the import of oslo_context has been aliased
to catch errors where context as variable is shadowed by the homonym
module.

Closes-bug: #1625135

Change-Id: I73127d7829c31ca66578eb8f7d76409b36c9dc6d

subject: Fix ML2 revision_number handling in port updates
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-09-23 12:03:49.000000000', 'files': ['neutron/tests/tempest/api/test_allowed_address_pair.py', 'neutron/tests/unit/plugins/ml2/test_plugin.py', 'neutron/plugins/ml2/plugin.py', 'neutron/tests/tempest/api/test_revisions.py'], 'message': "Fix ML2 revision_number handling in port updates

The revision number is bumped on the flush that changes
the port or a resource that bumps the port. However, in ML2
we create the dict that is used for after_update events,
mech driver calls, and the API response before all resource
modifications are complete so the dict may not reflect
the correct revision number.

This adjusts the update_port_status to flush changes to the
DB before constructing the dictionary response to give the
event listener a chance to bump the revision.

It also adjusts ML2 to update the 'updated_port' dict with
the latest result from make_port_dict after all of the related
objects have been processed to ensure the result has the latest
info from extensions. The API test for allowed address pairs
was adjusted to stop checking for order on update since no order
is stored in the DB.

The API test for revision numbers and ports was updated to
expect the correct behavior.

Closes-Bug: #1625981
Change-Id: I49d2d79a57d484fd98b8969f511895e607b7f128
(cherry picked from commit cb79d09e249a47d362706b2f4d64bd58c97c344f)
"}]
commit_message:
Fix ML2 revision_number handling in port updates

The revision number is bumped on the flush that changes
the port or a resource that bumps the port. However, in ML2
we create the dict that is used for after_update events,
mech driver calls, and the API response before all resource
modifications are complete so the dict may not reflect
the correct revision number.

This adjusts the update_port_status to flush changes to the
DB before constructing the dictionary response to give the
event listener a chance to bump the revision.

It also adjusts ML2 to update the 'updated_port' dict with
the latest result from make_port_dict after all of the related
objects have been processed to ensure the result has the latest
info from extensions. The API test for allowed address pairs
was adjusted to stop checking for order on update since no order
is stored in the DB.

The API test for revision numbers and ports was updated to
expect the correct behavior.

Closes-Bug: #1625981
Change-Id: I49d2d79a57d484fd98b8969f511895e607b7f128
(cherry picked from commit cb79d09e249a47d362706b2f4d64bd58c97c344f)

This patch fixes that by having the extension store the values requested

commit_message:
Fix ML2 test extension driver API test cases

The test cases were asserting bad behavior by the way the
test driver was designed. Rather than ensuring that the extension
was extending the resource in each case with the correct value,
it was asserting that different values came back from
update/create/show. In other words, it was asserting API
inconsistency which interferred with the dependent patch.

This patch fixes that by having the extension store the values requested
in the API and then use those same values for extending the result
whether it be for updates, creates, or shows.

Change-Id: Ib1517102e3fb776fca818acfddd9e0f733563fb3
Partial-Bug: #1625981
(cherry picked from commit 7e822960425326f26806bbfb650b8a844f38557d)

commit_message:
Ensure Win32 API calls do not block

Win32 API functions will be invoked, by default, using tpool.execute
when called from within a greenthread, ensuring that other
greenthreads are not blocked.

This workflow will not be applied to Win32 API functions that are
known to always return quickly, in which case this wouldn't bring
any benefit.

Closes-Bug: #1624364

Change-Id: I81a5a87558330b975bb0f40333689bdc7a5ce3e7
(cherry picked from commit 7335a39c9d11f0862f980de57ce3155c2a2d16eb)

commit_message:
Avoid using diskpart for disk rescans

At the moment, we're using diskpart for rescanning disks. Not only
this involves a process spawn overhead, but also this binary is
not available on Nano.

This change switches to the WMI equivalent method.

Closes-Bug: #1621361

Change-Id: Ifb780c331136adc3e6134bc29594d6da8344cfce
(cherry picked from commit f8152caf1c45603c3cd98fdcdb5de8fd12f516f9)

commit_message:
Moving of Ironic and Keystone scenarios into separate classes

Since current scenario implementation transforms method to class at runtime,
it is reasonable to have class-based scenario implementation which will be
much simpler to use behind the scenes.

This class should be based on Scenario and do not break compatibility.
The only required method is run() which is actually a body of scenario.

Change-Id: Ib4c2aa5651d8ac0750b937146e59376a7efcece0

revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2016-08-11 15:53:10.000000000', 'files': ['manila/tests/share/drivers/huawei/test_huawei_nas.py'], 'message': 'Fix the broken UT of huawei driver for py34/35

The cause of failing unit tests is a bug in huawei driver.
When huawei driver logins to backend, it reads username/password from
huawei configuration file. If the username/password are configured as
plain text, huawei driver'll encode them and overwrite the encoded text
to the configuration file.

The encoding logic code is like this:
  six.text_type(base64.b64encode("***"))

For py27, this code works fine. However, for py34, this text_type
converting adds some extra words to result unicode string, like
"b'***'"('***' is the actual encoded result string).
Once driver reads the username/password again, it'll get the incorrect
text and then fail while jsonutils.dumps.

All the failed unit tests tried to call login twice, and triggered the
error condition said above.

This patch is just a workaround, because those failed tests actually
no need to login twice, the redundant login calls are removed.

Another patch will be commited to fix the problem thoroughly in huawei
driver.  Bug https://launchpad.net/bugs/1612149 has been raised for
that work, and will also analyze what changed to trigger this issue
only recently.

Change-Id: Ia6bf7bbb9ffb9644085bbdf4f5576f09215a877f
Closes-Bug: #1612149
'}]
commit_message:
Fix the broken UT of huawei driver for py34/35

The cause of failing unit tests is a bug in huawei driver.
When huawei driver logins to backend, it reads username/password from
huawei configuration file. If the username/password are configured as
plain text, huawei driver'll encode them and overwrite the encoded text
to the configuration file.

The encoding logic code is like this:
  six.text_type(base64.b64encode("***"))

For py27, this code works fine. However, for py34, this text_type
converting adds some extra words to result unicode string, like
"b'***'"('***' is the actual encoded result string).
Once driver reads the username/password again, it'll get the incorrect
text and then fail while jsonutils.dumps.

All the failed unit tests tried to call login twice, and triggered the
error condition said above.

This patch is just a workaround, because those failed tests actually
no need to login twice, the redundant login calls are removed.

Another patch will be commited to fix the problem thoroughly in huawei
driver.  Bug https://launchpad.net/bugs/1612149 has been raised for
that work, and will also analyze what changed to trigger this issue
only recently.

Change-Id: Ia6bf7bbb9ffb9644085bbdf4f5576f09215a877f
Closes-Bug: #1612149

commit_message:
Add status field in the TaaS API

In the current implementation, when the TaaS API (tap-service,
tap-flow) call completes, the status of result is returned. [1]
In order to adopt an asynchronous model, the 'status' field is
needed in the API.
The following code adds the status field in the API.
In the first step, the status is set to 'ACTIVE' by default.

[1]: http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2016-March/090088.html

Depends-On: Ie6b3811e41a94721679c9178cdd5119bdad8208d
Change-Id: Ib8e4ad15e5b4272ac7f8800f72d7f2c003db798e

commit_message:
populate json with both 'project_id', 'tenant_id'

Neutron keyston v3 support is on-going [1].
From ODL perspective, it's simply variable rename from 'tenant_id'
to 'project_id'.
For ODL compatibility, populate json value for ODL neutron northbound
with both 'project_id' and 'tenant_id'.
Since ODL Neutron Northbound silently ignores unknown fields (more
precisely, Java jaxb does), it won't harm to have extra fields unknown
to ODL neutron northbound.

[1] https://specs.openstack.org/openstack/neutron-specs/specs/newton/moving-to-keystone-v3.html

Change-Id: Id1b18d76871edeab623f03d839616d6729a8dc73
Closes-Bug: #1616128

commit_message:
Add bigswitch command to compute rootwrap filters

'ivs-ctl' is called from the libvirt vif driver. While the filter exists
in network.filters, as the command is still used by nova compute it is
consistent to include it in compute.filters.

commit_message:
NetApp cDOT driver autosupport broken

The autosupport functionality of the NetApp cDOT driver is not working
with Python 2.7.12, the default in Xenial. Root cause is a deep copy
of the controller connection context, which includes some SSL context
stuff that doesn't play well with copy.deepcopy. So we can do a shallow
copy instead.

Change-Id: Ia2adc4ce27834e384e6d994fcb012ebf1d97c85c
Closes-Bug: #1621260

'message': 'plugins/xenserver: Add '.py' extension

All Python files, except executables, should have a '.py' extension.
This wasn't being done for files in the 'plugins/xenserver' folder,
likely because it seems unnatural to call a "plugin" with a file
extension.

Begin working towards a resolution for this by renaming all files to
include a '.py' extension. To avoid forcing operators to upgrade the
Nova service and per-host plugins at the same time, continue to
reference the old, non-'.py' filenames, using symlinks to ensure the
references continue to work. Once Ocata has been released, these
symlinks can be removed, the API version updated and the reference

commit_message:
plugins/xenserver: Add '.py' extension

All Python files, except executables, should have a '.py' extension.
This wasn't being done for files in the 'plugins/xenserver' folder,
likely because it seems unnatural to call a "plugin" with a file
extension.

Begin working towards a resolution for this by renaming all files to
include a '.py' extension. To avoid forcing operators to upgrade the
Nova service and per-host plugins at the same time, continue to
reference the old, non-'.py' filenames, using symlinks to ensure the
references continue to work. Once Ocata has been released, these
symlinks can be removed, the API version updated and the reference
updated to include the '.py' extension.

Change-Id: Icf4cf2424c15276a6c01778fb92f76bbdc9b2068
Closes-bug: #1302831

commit_message:
Force Ansible to use dynamic includes

Ansible 2.1.1 introduces a regression in the way conditional
includes are handled which results in every task in the
included file being evaluated even if the condition for the
include is not met. This extends the run time significantly
for a deployment.

This patch forces all conditional includes to be dynamic.

Change-Id: I864e5178f6cb8ca245bafbed9a94ae8d4ea29eae
Related-Bug: https://github.com/ansible/ansible/issues/17687

commit_message:
Provision from pre-cached/pre-downloaded CirrOS image

In run_tests.sh we symlink a cached image to /tmp/openstack/tempest
or it is downloaded to that location using wget which is more reliable.

Let's use that instead.

revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2016-09-20 19:09:46.000000000', 'files': ['elements/puppet-stack-config/puppet-stack-config.pp'], 'message': "Make puppet-stack-config.pp Puppet 4 compliant

- Zaqar instance needs to be a string with quotes or we get this error:
  Evaluation Error: Illegal title type at index 0. Expected String, got
  Integer
- Swift package resource name is actually swift and Puppet 4 needs to
  get the resource title, not the resource name.
  Same for nova-compute.
- Start nova-compute after nova-conductor. In Puppet 4, ordering
  matters, so let's move the order of Puppet class calls

Change-Id: Idaf36204d12c0c8730451b65babde3a7b935d673
"}]
commit_message:
Make puppet-stack-config.pp Puppet 4 compliant

- Zaqar instance needs to be a string with quotes or we get this error:
  Evaluation Error: Illegal title type at index 0. Expected String, got
  Integer
- Swift package resource name is actually swift and Puppet 4 needs to
  get the resource title, not the resource name.
  Same for nova-compute.
- Start nova-compute after nova-conductor. In Puppet 4, ordering
  matters, so let's move the order of Puppet class calls

Change-Id: Idaf36204d12c0c8730451b65babde3a7b935d673

requirements that are not in global requirements:
http://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack/monasca-statsd/tree/requirements.txt?h=stable/newton

This patch removes monasca-statsd from projects.txt for
stable/newton.

commit_message:
Pre-created port clean during subnet deletion

1. What is the problem
Before creating bottom subnet, we need to create some ports to
allocate ip address for bottom dhcp port and bottom gateway port.
These pre-created ports are not deleted after bottom resources
are deleted.

2. What is the solution to the problem
Clean these pre-created ports during top subnet deletion.

3. What the features need to be implemented to the Tricircle
   to realize the solution
Pre-created ports now can be cleaned up.

Change-Id: I73c0ef87e4104f1db9926a5972c5f36be94d724a

commit_message:
Remove unneeded try..except in heartbeat

as callback_url is now a required argument for this method,
there's no need for such check (presumably copy-pasted from
heartbeat-as-vendor-interface).

Besides, assigning a value to dictionary key never raises KeyError.

The now deprecated vendor heartbeat is unchanged.

Change-Id: Id1e1a15b2cbc5dfbae9655b0edbc30c0a0cf2c57

subject: Override credential key repository for null key tests
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-09-23 14:44:08.000000000', 'files': ['keystone/tests/unit/credential/test_fernet_provider.py'], 'message': "Override credential key repository for null key tests

The null key for credential encryption tests certain encryption
behavior when a key repository doesn't exist locally. If you were
to run these tests locally with a key repository created in the
default location (`/etc/keystone/credential-keys`) the tests would
fail.

This commit makes the null key tests override the key_repository location in
config, but doesn't actually create the repository - so the null key is infact
tested.

Change-Id: I9c970cd846da2f9d52547ecb7271a20791fb3301
"}]
commit_message:
Override credential key repository for null key tests

The null key for credential encryption tests certain encryption
behavior when a key repository doesn't exist locally. If you were
to run these tests locally with a key repository created in the
default location (`/etc/keystone/credential-keys`) the tests would
fail.

This commit makes the null key tests override the key_repository location in
config, but doesn't actually create the repository - so the null key is infact
tested.

Change-Id: I9c970cd846da2f9d52547ecb7271a20791fb3301
